src_text: Mengameli Cyril Ramaphosa ubite Lekgotla leKhabhinethi ngaLesine, mhla tinge-27 Bhimbidvwane 2022.
trg_text: President Cyril Ramaphosa convened the Cabinet Lekgotla on Thursday, 27 January 2022.

trg_text: The Cabinet Lekgotla deliberations are to inform government s priorities for the year ahead which President Ramaphosa will set out during the State of the Nation Address on Thursday, 10 February 2022.

src_text: Luhlelo Lwesigaba Lesibili le-SA Connect
trg_text: SA Connect

src_text: Ikhabhinethi ikuvumile kucala kwesigaba sesibili semklamo we-SA Connec Loluhlelo lutawenta Inchubomgomo ye-Inthanethi lesheshako yalelive isebente lekuyintfo leyavunywa yiKhabhinethi nga-2013.
trg_text: Cabinet approved the roll-out of the second phase of the SA Connect projec The plan gives effect to the country s Broadband Policy which was adopted by Cabinet in 2013.

src_text: Sigaba Sekucala sisebente njengemklamo wekuvisela wekunika tikhungo tahulumende letibalulekile letinge-970 tinsita te-inthanethi lesheshako te-10 Megabits (i-Mbps).
trg_text: Phase 1 served as a pilot phase to provide 10 Megabits (Mbps) broadband services to about 970 critical government facilitie

src_text: Lesigaba sesibili lesivunyiwe sitawetfulwa ngekusebentisa tikhungo tahulumende (Ejensi yeTebucwepheshe beteLwatiso lweMbuso [i-SITA]); i-Broadband Infraco ne-Sentech) kanye nemboni ye-inthanethi lesheshak Kuletinyanga letinge-36 letitako, lomklamo utawuchumanisa letikhungo tahulumende letisele, imimango kanye nemakhaya lasel
trg_text: The approved second phase will be rolled out using state-owned entities (State Information Technology Agency [SITA]); Broadband Infraco and Sentech) and the industr Over the next 36 months, the project will connect the remaining government facilities, communities and household

src_text: Lomklamo uyincenye yekutinikela kwahulumende kuvala ligebe letedijithali, ikakhulu emimangweni yasemaphandleni, kanye nekuchubela embili temnotfo wetedijithal Kuhlanganyela kwemkhakha lotimele nako kutawulungisa lokuhlelwa kabusha kwalomkhakha ngekufaka ekhatsi bonkhe bandlalindzima labafanele kulomkhakha wekuchumana ngetebucwephesh .
trg_text: The SA Connect project targets to achieve 80% broadband access in communities and government facilities over the next three years with a minimum speed capacity of 10Mbps per second and 100 Mbps for the high-demand facilitie

src_text: Lomklamo we-SA Connect uhlose kutsi i-inthanethi lesheshako ifinyelele imimango netikhungo tahulumende nge-80% kuleminyaka lemitsatfu letako ngesivinini selizingancane lesingu-10Mbps ngelisekhondi kanye ne-100 Mbps yetikhungo letidzinga kakhulu i-inthaneth
